The role of in situ generated H2S in preparation of Ag–S-Ga(OA)2 is validated by the comparative experiments with versus without degassing for H2S removal (Supplementary Figs. 3 and 4). Specifically, we prepare S-OAm stock solutions degassed at two different temperatures, i.e., room temperature (RT) and 130 °C (at which, the in situ generated H2S gas is degassed and collected in cold trap connected to the Schlenk line as yellowish-brown color) (Supplementary Figs. 3 and 4). These S-OAm stock solutions (degassed at RT versus 130 °C) are separately added into the reaction flasks containing Ag2S NPs and the reaction temperature is gradually elevated to 210 °C. Ag2S NPs mixed with S-OAm degassed at RT are decomposed into a form of AgSH (Ag2S NPs+H2S→AgSH\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
